caption:
UK RADIO: David Tennant Guests On Absolute Radio’s Hometime On Monday 

David Tennant will be making a welcome return to Absolute Radio on Monday when he appears on the station’s weekday drivetime show Hometime with Andy Bush and Richie Firth. Andy tweeted about this guest star earlier this evening: 

Andy Bush‏ @bushontheradio

Cheers for listening to Hometime this week, check out tonight’s podcast - we sing our own theme tune. Also, Monday’s show the amazing David Tennant is our special guest!

David’s appearance on Hometime is on air between 4pm to 7pm on Monday 4th February. For details of the differnt ways you can listen in click here.

summary: I had the b e s t Doctor Who related dream last night, where I was the Tenth Doctor’s companion, and at one point the Daleks...
body:
I had the b e s t Doctor Who related dream last night, where I was the Tenth Doctor’s companion, and at one point the Daleks stole the TARDIS. And we were momentarily panicked, but then we just found it, abandoned on a street corner. So for a minute we were like ‘crisis averted’, but then the Daleks just kept showing up in a TARDIS, sometimes multiple Daleks in multiple Police Boxes.

And we figured out, the Daleks had gone time travelling all over during the (from our point of view) brief time they had the TARDIS, and now were just trying to kill us repeatedly - as in, they’d show up, try and kill us, and when we got away they’d just get back in the time machine and try again.

And the Doctor was like “This must work out ok because, like, we found the TARDIS without any Daleks in it. So at some point we must win and get them to vacate the TARDIS… right?”

My alarm went off before the conclusion, which I bet the dream-writer part of my brain was super happy about, because I don’t know how the hell I was gonna resolve that timey-wimey plot.
